By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Nigeria on Saturday recorded 110 new cases of COVID-19 infections, bringing the total confirmed cases in the country to 67,330, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. This is also as the Centre has informed that a total of 62,819 patients have been treated and discharged from various isolation centres across the country. The health agency in a report released via twitter handle said that 1,171 persons have died of the novel virus since the index case was reported in the country on February 27, 2020. The NCDC  said the states (including FCT) where the new infections were recorded are as follows: Lagos-26FCT-23Kaduna-20Katsina-11Ogun-7Ekiti-6Plateau-5Rivers-4Kano-3Nasarawa-3Niger-2 See the state by state breakdown of the total confirmed cases: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria, the most populous country in africa on Monday recorded 56 new cases of #COVID-19, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. The report released by the NCDC said this brought the total confirmed cases in the country to 66,439 out of… November 24, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID-19 in Nigeria recorded 106 infections on Friday as the Centre for Disease Control confirmed 170 new cases of the novel virus. This renewed upsurge in number of infections in Lagos may not be unconnected with the large… October 31, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  The latest report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control says that Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID-19 infection  accounted for 52.2percent of 136 new confirmed cases recorded on Monday in Nigeria. The health agency's report released via twitter handle stated that… September 29, 2020 In "Top Stories"